### Core functions — implement all with these exact signatures

**`pingHealth()`** — `fetch(apiBase() + '/health')`, update dot class and text. Called on load + every 30s.

**`loadTables()`** — `GET /tables`, calls `renderTableList(tables)`.

**`renderTableList(tables)`** — if empty show placeholder. Each item: table name in `font-mono` + version badge. Click → `loadTableDetail(alias, el)`.

**`loadTableDetail(alias, el)`** — toggle `.active`. If editor is blank or starts with `SELECT * FROM`, insert `SELECT *\nFROM {alias}\nLIMIT 100`. `GET /tables/{alias}` → render schema fields (name + type) + Refresh/Remove buttons.

**`runQuery(page?)`** — posts to `/query`, calls `renderResults(data)` on success, `showError(data.detail)` on failure. Shows spinner during execution. Disables Run button.

**`renderResults(data)`** — builds `<table class="results">`. Cell typing: number → `.num` (amber), `true/false` → `.bool-t/.bool-f`, null → `.null` + text "NULL". Calls `renderPagination(data)`.

**`renderPagination(data)`** — smart page range via `getPageRange(current, total)`. Shows `‹` / `›` prev/next, ellipsis gaps between page clusters. Each page button calls `runQuery(p)`.

**`getPageRange(current, total)`** — returns union of: `{1, total, current, current±1, current±2}`, sorted.

**`runBenchmark()`** — `POST /query/benchmark?sql=...&page=1&page_size=100`, calls `renderBenchmark(data)`.

**`renderBenchmark(data)`** — for each engine result: bar width = `(elapsed_ms / max_ms) * 100%`. Assign `bench-rank-1/2/3` classes for top 3 (adds 🥇🥈🥉 via CSS `::before`). Show error text for failed engines.

**`exportData(fmt)`** — builds URL `GET /query/export?sql=...&fmt=...&engine=...`, creates `<a>` element and `.click()`.

**`changePageSize()`** — updates `state.pageSize`, re-runs `runQuery(1)` if `state.lastSQL` exists.

**`switchTab(tab)`** — toggles `.active` on `.tab` elements and `#tab-{name}` content divs.

**`showError(detail)` / `hideError()`** — shows/hides `#errorBanner` with `error_code` + message.

**`fmtBytes(b)`** — formats bytes to B/KB/MB/GB with 1–2 decimal places.

**`openAddModal()` / `closeModal(id)`** — toggle `.show` class on modal backdrop.

**`submitAddTable()`** — validates alias + path required. Parses storage options as JSON. `POST /tables`. On success: close modal, `loadTables()`, clear form fields.

